Name: extraskeletal mesenchymal chondrosarcoma
Definition: An adult sarcoma of soft tissue and mesenchymal chondrosarcoma that is located_in the cartilage.

Name: extraskeletal myxoid chondrosarcoma
Definition: An extraosseous chondrosarcoma that has_material_basis_in cells derived from transformed cells that produce cartilage and is characterized by a marked abundance of extracellular mucoid (myxoid) matrix.

Name: adult extraosseous chondrosarcoma
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that involves infestation of mites belonging to the family Sarcoptidae

Name: intracranial chondrosarcoma
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that involves infestation of mites belonging to the family Sarcoptidae
